article.description: Jaren English had 17 points as Saint Bonaventure rolled past Hofstra 73-45 on Saturday.
article.headline: English lifts St. Bonaventure over Hofstra 73-45
article.linkText: English lifts St. Bonaventure over Hofstra 73-45
article.story: ST. BONAVENTURE, N.Y. -- Jaren English had 17 points as Saint Bonaventure rolled past Hofstra 73-45 on Saturday. Dominick Welch had 17 points and six rebounds for Saint Bonaventure (5-4), which earned its fourth straight win. Bobby Planutis added 11 points, eight rebounds and five assists. Osun Osunniyi had 8 points and 16 rebounds and Kyle Lofton had a career-high 11 assists. Hofstra totaled 26 first-half points, a season low for the team. Desure Buie had 17 points for the Pride (6-4). Saint Bonaventure faces Gannon at home next Saturday. Hofstra plays Stony Brook at home on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
